Sentencas: Sr0.9Ce0.1Co0.9Nb0.1O3-delta(SCCN) has been synthesized using solid state reaction, and investigated as a new cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (ITSOFCs).
Titulo: Cerium and niobium doped SrCoO3-δ as a potential cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SCCN material exhibits sufficiently high electronic conductivity and excellent chemical compatibility with SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Cerium and niobium doped SrCoO3-δ as a potential cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Highly charged Ce4+ and Nb5+ successfully stabilize the perovskite structure to avoid order-disorder phase transition.
Titulo: Cerium and niobium doped SrCoO3-δ as a potential cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity reaches a high value of 516 S cm(-1) at 300 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Cerium and niobium doped SrCoO3-δ as a potential cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistances of the SCCN-50 wt.% Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) cathode are as low as 0.027, 0.049, and 0.094 Omega cm(2) at 700, 650, and 600 degrees C, respectively, with the corresponding peak power densities of 1074, 905, and 589 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Cerium and niobium doped SrCoO3-δ as a potential cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A relatively low thermal expansion coefficient of SCCN-SDC is 14.3 x 10(-6) K-1 in air.
Titulo: Cerium and niobium doped SrCoO3-δ as a potential cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All these results imply that SCCN holds tremendous promise as a cathode material for ITSOFCs.
Titulo: Cerium and niobium doped SrCoO3-δ as a potential cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
